hat seem to not have much in common, Ang reveals how they share very similar ways of conceptualizing race and sheds light on an emerging global story of value.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAmerican fictionxAsian American authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aAsians in literature. 0aMalaysian fictionxHistory and criticism. 0aRace in literature. 0aRacism in literature. 4aAmerican Studies : Asian American Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aLiterature : American Literature. 4aLiterature : Multiethnic Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / Asian American.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847502840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438475028423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438475028/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles